Decent sushi. Not the best but definitely not the worst. One thing that really drives me crazy, and that is not unique to Nori, is if you want sashimi (no rice) you are required to get two pieces at an additional price. This makes no sense to me. It limits the variety I can choose in the amount I want to eat. What is the difference? A slice of fish is a slice of fish.
Great lunch special on week days... 50% off original maki.
Easy pickup and great prices
Excellent customer service. Sushi was delicious.  People are polite. Everything was delicious and amazing! Please come and visit.

This restaurant is my number one restaurant.  Of all restaurants I know I love it most. I never miss an opportunity to go to that place. when  I want to go to a superb supper, this restaurant comes first to my head. superb and all sorts of  food and a rich menu.generous team, and great ambience. Also, the tariff is decent. I tell about this spot with pleasure.

First to say there is no parking so first come first serve. The menu is quite simple order the top right corner with a beer to make your visit a good one. The toro rolls we're awesome the chefs kept piling on the rolls so crab actually blue crab were the joint. Siting arrangement are slim but the food and drinks for 5 bucks for Sapporo and to too top off the night take home menu with Nigori.
Love their concept of fast food. Absolutely delicious handrolls at very reasonable price set up. Very crispy flavorful seaweed with warm fresh rice is the best. Definitely will be back.
Staff was kind and the fish was fresh - what more can you ask for!
The service was god awful, the food was decent, would not come here again
The sushi is great. Always fresh and great flavors but the service is lacking
If you want to spend 16 dollars for salmon teriyaki that is the size of a kids meal, then this is the place for you.
This place is amazing! Great quality, well prepared, thoughtful recipes! Yum!

Very disappointed!! The food was below average... Karaage chicken was tasteless ( need to be marinated: soy, sake, ginger, garlic etc...)  the quality of the ingredients  where not the best! Will not order again. Where is the love ?
Excellent Maki
Surely a place worth stopping over, the food is fantastic and well prepared, the rates are reasonable and it is constantly well kept here. Keep it up.
I admire this place a lot. theres a unique ambiance. The cuisine is good. the service is powerful and the team is well trained. The price is fair. I definitely recommend.
The service is regularly swift, awesome mood, very nice employees. I will visit here again when I arrive nearby.

We came to this restaurant for a meeting. we heard about this spot from quite a few people.  Well, it was a winning. The crew were very polite and we had an excellent feeling. The meal was fresh and delicious. We had a great time and we shall definitely come back again. We recommend this place to all.

We love eating out. Yesterday we  visited this fine place which friends recommended to us. We passed a delightful experience there with very good meal and an efficient team and  a professional chief cook. We  added this restaurant in our list  and we will surely come back very soon.  Highly recommended.
This spot is awesome! Reasonable pricing, big dishes and the staff members are regularly very kind.
My husband and I have been coming to Nori for almost ten years. Everything is so good and the staff is so friendly. It's my favorite neighborhood spot.
The food is great very affordable great sevice good vibes b.y.o.b and its a good time Monday half price specials..
Best sushi restaurant ever. Beginner sushi eater friendly too

My husband and I found our favorite sushi place!!! Non-crowded (the days we’ve been there) cozy, BYOB 🙌🏻 and although we never tried raw fish, the waitress was kind enough to make some recommendations and we loved it!!! Monday’s sushi is 1/2 off so a plus! Service is great, food is great and environment great!!! A must wicker well place to try!
Great food, server could stand to speak up. 🍻
Great service!

(Original) Pedimos mucho sushis al centro, es lo mejor para compartir, pidan la gyoza soup, está muy rica, además puedes llevar tus bebidas.
Nori is a neighborhood favorite. Don't be fooled by the newer glitzyer competitors. Also Noris half off Mondays are unbeatable in sushi value.

I've never had a bad meal at Nori Sushi. The food is always fresh and very flavorful. The staff is also very pleasant and helpful. It's in the fun Wicker Park neighborhood. If you haven't been, it's kind of like a hipster neighborhood with many different restaurants, bars, and vintage stores.
They refused to seat us. I don't know why. They got 2 tables for people that got into restaurant after us. we asked and they said they had resos and clearly wasn't the case.
I have been here countless times! Always good! Now they have the best help!!! Try the “WickerPark “  and the “ caterpillar”
Good food
Takoyaki was really good

Great sushi place in Wicker park that features Half priced Maki for lunch. Beautiful plate presentation, and BYOB. A very chill atmosphere thats a great location for people watching and outdoor seating.  Service is fast and the food is excellent well prepared. Overall a flawless experience.

Food is good, but only worth the price when it is half off. They play good music, but the environment seemed to lack in decoration. Tinted windows make the restaurant seem closed/secluded despite being in the corner. With many Asian restaurants in the area, this place would not likely be someone's first pick.
seemingly low quality fish. somehow all my nigiri had a dry mouth feel. not recommended.
Fun little shop for 🍣 on the go. You can stay and eat with a BYOB of your choosing making it a hard place not to like. Fairly inexpensive for sushi so dontd compare it to a five 🌟 restaurant

Great lunch specials.  Usually no wait.  Decent prices.  Great place to save a few bucks in Wicker.  I enjoyed the food.  Right by wood street,  it's accessible via bike, car,  and public transportation.  I would eat here again.
Great service! The fish was fresh and loved the decor!
Good sushi and Thai iced tea
White voice on at all times here"Societal racism". The waitress are also short & rude
Great food. Nice quite place fir a.date night.
$7.75 for a small bowl of broth and 2 shrimps ...
A top 3 fav of the area

Good deal when you go during 1/2 price days/time. However I find really annoying that they never bring my change back (this happened over 6 times in the last half a year). Who presumes a costumer is leaving over a 50% tip and not wanting the change back? Do I really need to ask back my change every single time??? It is really annoying!
Love their sushi & their service!
Loved the takoyaki!

I find everything here to be extremely fresh and I highly recommend everyone to come here on a Monday when most of their maki rolls are half off.  I love to come here at lunch hour to order the sushi/s as sashimi bento box priced well at $12  or I'll order the spicy tuna bowl with cold sushi rice priced for just $10 with a maki roll which is half off at lunchtime.  Sadly they are closed on Tuesday.  They have excellent thai iced tea here but I wasn't blown away by the iced thai coffee.   I've eaten here 6 or more times because it's relaxing to sit outside and have fresh sashimi while people watching in Wicker Park.   Best value is lunch hour so take advantage of the patio before summer slips away.
I never leave reviews but that was the worst sushi I ever had.
First time trying sushi. Also had Spicy crispy noodles. Very good with specials on Mondays.

I have mixed feelings about this place. I got recommended to go here for the sushi, but the smoked salmon roll I ordered was small and underwhelming. I have had better Tonkotsu ramen at other places. What I can recommend from here is the Thai Iced Tea, loved the flavor. Overall, the atmosphere was nice and service was fine, but I do think that some of the food is overpriced.
Good sushi but a little pricey for the quality. Miss their half off deals.
Love the food here. Service is great and the vibe of the restaurant is super comfortable!
Delicious vege maki rolls, also loved the Thai milk tea. Friendly staff. Thanks for the meal. :)
Love the atmosphere and great menu selection.  Food was delicious and service was great.  A must try when in the area.
Excellent food!
The sushi is awesome and it is not too expensive. My favorite spot for sushi in wicker Park.
Half off nori maki on Monday when paying in cash. Tremendous deal.

Pretty bad the rice was soggy and one of the Rolls was way over sized. The rolls weren’t even close to being rolled properly super squishy and impossible to pick up with chopsticks. We only ate about half and tossed the rest. Sad
Sushi was fine. Soup was benign.  A bit pricey for what it is.
One word: average.
Very nice atmosphere.
Great sushi
Delicious
Been there 2x, don't plan on going again.  Had Spicy Tuna Rolls, Philly Rolls and Shrimp Fried Rice.  Food is bland and underwhelming, mediocre at best
Reasonable price, reasonable quality. BYOB. Great half price options for Sunday lunch!
Favorite sushi place in the city! Delicious!

We came here for their half-off sushi on Monday. We ordered the dragon roll, spicy tuna, salmon skin, rainbow roll, and others. The sushi was solid.  Get the spicy mayo sauce on the side -- it's dope. This place is BYOB too, which is awesome!
Very average sushi and not cheap
great place. especially monday 1/2 off sushi special is awasome

I love the food and the venue it absolutely beautiful. Very clean and nice staff. Only downside is the high prices, which is understandable considering the quality. However it would be great if there were more specials like half-off days or simple discounts on certain menu items. Other than that Nori Sushi is my go-to sushi place ❤️
Best lunch spot. 1/2 off their maki.
Sushi by the piece isn't my thing tbh
Really good makis.
Great service and the restaurant possesses a colorful urban atmosphere. Love the seaweed salad but wished there were larger portions.
Great food. Fast service. Good prices
My server was great and the food is ok for the asking price
Food is spectacular calamari sushi grade prices

Monday they have 1/2 price house rolls. Obviously they aren't the top line rolls, but a good deal regardless. They are also Cash only if you're taking advantage of the deal.  Lots of delivery comes out of here but I can't speak to the quality.
Great sushi at a great price

Called in 15 minutes before closing time to place a Togo order. I wanted one California roll(6 pieces) the lady on the phone refused to take my order and told me they were closed. I told her I was just around the corner, no more than a 5 minute walk and she refused to serve me. I asked her if I could come in and place my order instead since she wouldn't take my order over the phone and she told me everyday they close 20 minutes early. I've only been here one other time and the service was awful so I thought I would try it again. Let's just say they won't be getting my business anymore and I'll be sure to tell my friends how rude and unprofessional this place is.
Great place to bring a date
The manager should be fired for his behavior. Will not recommend to anyone.
Simply great.
Good food. Good service and beautiful views.
We been there few times. Good sushi place. Nothing exceptional, but worth a visit
Great place for sushi at reasonable prices

Good Sushi Spot a lil pricey considering the lack of ambiance and comfortable seating. Rolls range from $7-15 which is average but other restaurants are more comfortable. Nori is more like a take n'go or counter place with a few tables.  That said however the service was very attentive,  friendly, and quick - which I do appreciate and will have me coming back for more.  Wide selection of Asian foods on the menu as well not just a sushi place.

Borderline terrible service and experience...From the get go we didn't have anyone come take our order or even bring us a glass of water.  It took about 10 minutes before I  had to get up and ask someone to come over to our table and take our order...After the fact the server poured us some warm water that supposedly  had been sitting out and had no ice in it. So I ended up having to ask her to bring some fresh water with ice in it...lol...seriously??  The sushi itself was just ok...definitely not the best I've had although some of their choices seemed appealing. The rice wasn't fresh and the taste was just off...I ordered the Tokyo and the Dragon. Honestly, I enjoyed the appetizers much more than I did the sushi...In all the service was the worst part of the experience. I went at around 5pm on Tuesday with my girlfriend. There wasn't alot of people there but the servers acted like they weren't on the clock. The one girI  I had to ask to service my table was on her phone the entire time I was there...Anytime I needed anything, I had to get up and ask someone for service, not once did anyone come over to ask me how was everything, or if I needed anything...The only thing I didnt have to get up for was the bill...that they brought without me having to ask...how ironic...  I'm glad to say I won't be coming back there anytime soon if it all...probably the worst sushi and the worst experience I've ever had.
Good food good prices
BYOB Sushi space, small and quiet.

The sushi is nice and varied and plenty of interesting veggie choices. However kinda pricey and portion sizes tiny for the price. Got takeout, maybe better dine in for value, but personally thought it wasn't great value

Great standing special , 50% off a page of Maki during lunch.  And a yelp check- in coupon for the other times.  The sashimi they comped for making me wait for a roll was the best flavor of the meal and showed a generous spirit.   Server was Chicago nice.  (I.e. not the outstanding professional I always hope for but she gave no grief and got the job done)  Not a destination sushi spot in my eyes, but the deal let's one eat well at a competitive price.  (Review based on first visit.)
Fantastic crunch spicy tuna!
Great sushi!
Delicious food, great deals!! Love it.
Borderline digesting quolity of severely overpriced  sushi and sashimi, which is 1/2 off on Mondays. Waiters incompetence was certainly noticible. Overall - sad.

Horrible dinner tonight. It was 10:05 and me and my girlfriends were finishing our dinner and this supposedly "manager" said, "we're closing you guys can go home now."  Um, excuse me. That was rude and very unprofessional and I let her know it.  She told us we were an hour late to our reservation and in reality, we were there on time only 2/8 people were late to order. She had no respect and was very rude. She was talking back to us after I called her out about not talking to us in such a rude manner.  I love the waitress who attended us. And I love the sushi there. She just made our experience horrible. It's this  caucasian young woman with brown hair with bangs. I asked who the manager was and she said she was. I'm gonna get to the bottom of this. I don't want other people to experience this.
Good sushi place that always has a crowd.
good sushi, but kind of expensive for what it is.  cool atmosphere though.
One of Our favorite Sushi places! Great presentation, very tasty and fresh sushi and warm and friendly staff! Keep up the fresh sushi coming! 🌎
Delicious food, great service, and friendly service.
A solid sushi place. Can always find a seat at the bar and its fun to watch them make stuff.

Great place-quick service during the off-peak hours. Great sushi. Way better than Papajin. Red Nori and Grand Caribbean rolls are outstanding. My friend got the teriyaki chicken, with which I think he was satisfied. Miso soup is good too. Completely BYOB, but there is a Walgreens across the street that sells alcohol. I recommend picking up a bottle of wine.

Great casual spot! They have half priced maki on Mondays which is a fantastic deal. It also doesn't hurt that it's BYOB. If you're looking for a casual spot to grab some sushi, this is your place! It tends to be busy on Mondays for the deal, so expect to wait a little bit.
A+ best of the best

The wife had been bugging me about trying Nori, so we did. We had a reservation and was seated immediately. The server was a little terse at first, then she got a lot more terse. The wife and I ordered, I used the Japanese words on the menu to order my meal, the wife just spoke in english. When we got our food, the wife one extra piece of sushi. She asked what was that, the server told her and the wife said she did not order that. The server said I read back to you what you ordered, and the wife told her you said in in Japanese, I was not clear what you were saying. Wife said fine I will keep it, the server got all huffy and took it back, started complaining about losing money on that piece. It cost $3.50, is that worth alienating customers? We got a new server and everything was great after that. The food was delicious, and we got a free roll. We liked the place, and we will definitely go back, we just do not want that server again.
Good place, had quality deals and clean fish. Staff is friendly, pretty, informed and fast even during rush.

Came here with a Groupon, and Nori is the rare place that I would return WITHOUT a Groupon.  The Fire Dragon is one of the top rolls I've had in Chicago.  BYOB without a corking fee completes the experience.  The weekday specials (half off sushi on Mondays) makes Nori a regular stop for a sushi fix.  Reservations recommended Fri-Sun.
The service was quick and friendly. Nothing particularly outstanding about this place, but the food is good. BYOB, which is a plus.
Half off sushi every monday thru friday for happy hour.... need I say more? The sushi here is amazing!!
What a great place to stop  in for lunch.  The daily deals are great.  And the bring your own is a nice feature.  The Divvy station is close by which is very handy.  A great eating place.

Pretty affordable for a sushi place and they always have special deals (on Monday the regular rolls are half off). The people are generally friendly, though sometimes you have to wave them down to get your check. Best of all it's BYO!  So bring some friends (but not too many, because I'll want a seat too) and have a fun night out. You can make reservations, and sometimes you need to to get a seat easily.
the sushi is just amazing, good environment, good food and the best part of it, is that you can bring your own alcohol, love it

I came here with Groupon. Overall I had a pleasant experience, but though the sushi was too sweet and a bit too Americanized. The sauces feels drenched with sugar. The staff was friendly. The price was more than what I would pay for but their Monday half off is a good deal and so is the lunch special. I would consider coming here when there are specials.
This place has the best Ramen noodle dish ever! The service is a bit shotty, pretty sure our waitress hated us. Byob place, which is great! We drank Miller High Life with our sushi!
This is my go to sushi place in Wicker Park/Bucktown. I've been to most in the area and this one is definately the best for sure! BYOB, fresh sushi and great service. Half off makis on Monday!

Our fav sushi in Chicago. The strawberry sundae is my favorite sushi roll of all time!!!! Had the Chicago roll for the first time last week, and will def be going back for it. The atmosphere is killer and can't wait to sit on the patio this summer.

it's right at the corner of my old apartment and definitely a place to go in wicker park. it has good sushi and my favorite garlic fried rice. the environment is nice as well, in summer you will be able to seat outdoor and enjoy the breeze of summer nights. if you order online for the first time, you will get a 10% discount for your order as well. i found this secret from the pen they gave me as promotion.

I started with the Calamari Honey Wasabi appetizer which was decent. I thought there was too much breading so it soaked up a lot of grease which made it lose some of the calamari flavor. Next, I warmed myself up with a cup of delicious Miso soup, this hit the spot on a bitter cold Chicago winter night.  I had the following rolls: Crunchy Spicy Tuna - decent, not as flavorful as other Spicy Tuna rolls I've had Maki, Grand Caribbean - fruity & sweet, makes it lose the fish flavor Monster - My favorite out of the 3, good spice to it  I used a Groupon which made it worth coming and it is BYOB. I would come back and try some other items. This is a good middle of the road Sushi establishment.
Great neighborhood spot. Excellent specialty rolls. Try the Fire Dragon and the Red Nori. Nice staff, and BYOB!
